cxro.common.device.axis

Class IaiAxis

  • java.lang.Object
    • cxro.common.device.axis.AbstractAxis
      • cxro.common.device.axis.IaiAxis
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Axis

    public final class IaiAxis
extends AbstractAxis
    Device handler for IAI Modbus axis controller.

    The IAI controller is located on an RS-485 2W network and uses the Modbus/RTU protocol. This device handler expects that it communicates with the controller via a Moxa MB3170 Modbus/TCP gateway. Each controller is assigned an individual Modbus/TCP connection.

    The IAI RS-485 network supports up to 16 controllers. The Moxa MB3170 supports up to 32 simultaneous connections.

      • getSwitches

        public boolean[] getSwitches()
                      throws java.io.IOException
        Description copied from interface: Axis
        This method returns an array of booleans that represent the current status of the hardware switches on the controller.

        They are in the form: {Reverse_Switch, Forward_Switch, Home_Switch}.
        When true, the switch is active.

        Ex:
           switches[] = xAxis.getRawSwitches();
           if(switches[1]) // test Forward_Switch
             //throw error or act accordingly.

        Specified by:
        getSwitches in interface Axis
        Specified by:

        switch array.
